"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-new-250-000-tickets-for-paris-olympics-2024-to-be-released-organisers-confirmed\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbNew tickets for Paris Olympics 2024 to be released  Fans will have a new chance to buy 250 000 new tickets for the Paris Olympics 2024 next week - but they will need to be quick!  Fans will have a new chance to buy tickets for theParis Olympics2024next week with another250 000places set to be released, chief organiserTony Estanguetsaid on Wednesday.  \\\"Next week, on April 17 at 10:00, we will put 250 000 new tickets on sale for all sports, all price categories and for all competition sites,\\\" Estanguet told reporters.  Following criticism of high prices during previous releases, he said that half of them would be sold for under \\u20ac100 (R2 016).  A total of 10 000 tickets for gymnastics will be made available, with 15 000 for swimming, 12 000 for tennis and 35 000 for beach volleyball, which is set to be played in a temporary stadium in front of the Eiffel Tower.  \\\"You will have to be quick,\\\" Estanguet warned, adding that the vast majority of tickets - 7.9 million in total - had already been sold.  Two-thirds of previous buyers were French, but people from 150 different countries have also secured tickets, according to the organising committee.  TheParis Olympicsare set to take place fromJuly 26-August 11followed by the Paralympics from August 28-September 8.  By Garrin Lambley \\u00a9 Agence France-Presse  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"